Interface Channel

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Actor, MessageReceiver, Snapshot, Staleable

    public interface Channel
extends MessageReceiver, Staleable
    Represents an IRC channel.

        @Nonnull
Optional<User> getUser(@Nonnull
                                 String nick)
        Gets a user by their nick, if they are known to the client. Note that the server may not have sent the User data over, while the nickname may be known to the channel.
        Parameters:
        nick - user's nick
        Returns:
        the user object, if known
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if nick is null
        See Also:
        hasCompleteUserData(), ChannelUsersUpdatedEvent

      • getUsers

        @Nonnull
List<User> getUsers()
        Gets all Users known to be in the channel. Note that the server may not have sent all User data over, while the nickname may be known to the channel. If you just want a list of nicknames, see getNicknames().
        Returns:
        users in the channel
        See Also:
        hasCompleteUserData(), ChannelUsersUpdatedEvent
